Argued and submitted October 31, STATE OF OREGON, Respondent, v. CONNIE HAROLD MARET, JR., Appellant. (CF95-0033; CA A90085) 928 P2d 355 Dan Maloney, Deputy Public Defender, argued the cause for appellant. With him on the brief was Sally L. Avera, Public Defender. Timothy A. Sylwester, Assistant Attorney General, argued the cause for respondent. With him on the brief were Theodore R. Kulongoski, Attorney General, and Virginia L. Linder, Solicitor General. PER CURIAM

conviction affirmed; remanded with instructions November 27, 1996

Before Deits, Presiding Judge, and De Muniz and Haselton, Judges.
